              "text": "The Digo inheritance system is built on a principle that confounds outsiders accustomed to single-track descent: a person inherits through both their mother and their father, but from different categories of property and under different rules. This is not a contradiction — it is a dual system refined over centuries, in which the matrilineal fuko and the patrilineal mbari each govern distinct domains of wealth, obligation, and identity."
